verbose_text: Interestingly, in the subset of 39 PTEN-no-expression patients, in which the confounding effect of PTEN on PD-L1 is controlled, PD-L1 expression was no longer associated with distant metastasis (P = 0.102), TNM stage (P = 0.634), and survival analysis showed that there was no significant difference in the overall survival between the PD-L1-higher-expression group and PD-L1-lower-expression group (XREF_FIG, chi2 = 0.494, P = 0.482).
